<item>
            <title>[JCR-1800] JCR2SPI: lockmgr isn&apos;t aware about external unlock (CacheBehavior.OBSERVATION)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1800</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>issue occurring with CacheBehavior.OBSERVATION only:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
the lock manager expects the jcr:lockIsDeep property to be created upon successful lock.&lt;br/&gt;
this however isn&amp;#39;t the case since the time, we changed the Operation.persisted method to invalidate the affected states. consequently the mgr never started to listen on changes made to the jcr:lockIsDeep property and consequently wasn&amp;#39;t aware of an external removal.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
suggested fix:&lt;br/&gt;
force re-loading of the lock holding node.</description>
